parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or lock up, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The power steering warning light is illuminated
the steering wheel is hard to turn or locks up
the steering wheel shakes or vibrates
the vehicle is difficult to control
and the power steering system fails intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering gear assembly can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or lock up, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel is hard to turn
the steering wheel locks up
the vehicle is difficult to control
and the steering gear assembly fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The brake lights are illuminated
the ABS light is illuminated
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
and the vehicle is difficult to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning brake lights can cause confusion to other drivers, leading to potential accidents, and also affect the cruise control system.
symptoms: Brake lights stay on all the time
brake lights do not illuminate when the brake pedal is depressed
brake lights illuminate when the brake pedal is not depressed
cruise control does not engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel pump leakage can cause a strong odor of gas, which can lead to headaches and discomfort, and also pose a fire hazard.
symptoms: Strong odor of gas
gas leak from the back of the car
fuel pump leakage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight bulb can reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night.
symptoms: Headlight bulb keeps burning out
bulb harness melting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent electrical failures can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or experience strange electrical behavior, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
loses power
or experiences strange electrical behavior
such as flashing lights
malfunctioning gauges
or failure to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning brake lights can cause confusion or miscommunication with other drivers, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake lights stay on when the brake pedal is not depressed
or they do not come on when the brake pedal is pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning cruise control can cause the vehicle to suddenly accelerate or decelerate, leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: The cruise control disengages unexpectedly
or it comes on when the brake pedal is pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The BCM failure can cause a range of electrical system malfunctions, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences strange electrical behavior
such as malfunctioning gauges
flashing lights
or failure to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The water leak can cause electrical system malfunctions, corrosion, or damage to the vehicle's interior, leading to safety hazards or costly repairs.
symptoms: Water pours into the vehicle from the interior lights
causing electrical system malfunctions or damage to the vehicle's interior.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ignition system failure can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or fails to start
or the ignition key becomes stuck in the ignition.
